Prosecutor Karim Khalil QC had previously told the court that the cause of the baby's death was a head injury although there were 'signs of numerous other inflicted injuries too'.

He added: 'Baby Aukse was a helpless infant, entirely dependent upon the love and care of her parents.

'She suffered very serious and extensive injuries - to her head and body, both externally and internally.

'The nature of these injuries tells you what the person who inflicted them intended.

'All those injuries occurred when she was in the sole care of her father.

'As he committed those acts of violence against Baby Aukse, he must have intended to kill her or to cause her really serious harm - that is murder.' 

 

